        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Err.. Ok, What I meant was to have a CLASS SKILL of summoning a vampire pet since almost all the class skills of a necro is useless in most situations. Having a pet that is raid oriented for a necro will certainly improve our class's acceptance to a raid. Does any of you ever see more than 2-3 necros at a raid? On my server we have only 1 most of the time and at most 3. What about the rest of the classes? Having a pet class skill that is available at lvl 59(assuming you're getting class skills before getting 60) is certainly not overpowering at all, and quite reasonable if anyone even have a small understanding of how useless necros are at a raid(not solo'ing mind you, although many classes are overtaking us as better solo'ers).</P><P>And it's not impossible for VI to institute the pet as a class skill. Making changes to what is already for us, like duck scythe(not staff) or spectre pet will take alot of coding and tracing back to where programmers have left off or forgotten. Only thing to fear is(if they accept and is willing to improve the playability of necromancers for raids) making the pet too easily killed during raids by AE/riposte or it being not worth the effort of summoning at all.</P><P>Therefore I suggested a vampire pet. It signifies status. What will you feel if you have a spectre pet and the necro besides you have a slutty vampire with blood on it's mouth? Make it 10 peridots and you will still see me having that vampire following me everywhere. Making the pet's name same as a beastlord's, a buff. Maybe not the same like Soandso's warder, some other tittle could sounds more original. They're definitely not going to make it hit for 100+ for sure, so it could be better if the pet flurries. Soandso's vampire lands a flurry of attacks on Target! Sounds cool right? Flurries doesn't always go off, and when it does it doesn't really do alot of damage for a pet hitting for even 60s but it certainly improve necromancers by a mile and everyone will be impressed by the looks and flurries. The hard part is making the pet more raid oriented, high resists, immune to fear or more hp could be the key to it.</P><P>It sounds alot to ask for, but if they really do it, I can forsee necros will be much more useful in more situations while not making us too powerful compared to other classes. </P><P>In fact they would be giving us having better graphics while improving our damge output by some, depending on how much the pet will be hitting for. The main point is to making a pet useable during raids which is quite tough to get as a class skill. Rogues and wizards will still be doing more damage, shamans will still be solo'ing better than us with their slows and malo, clerics and warriors will still be more needed at raids and monks will still be pulling better than us. Not overpowering at all, just takes a bit of efforts to make us necros much more fun. Sorry for the long post.</P><P><BR>Janee the Heretic<BR>Tholuxe Paells<BR>Intrepid<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
