        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Simple reason why your argument is wrong, Euri:</P><P>Epic should NEVER, EVER be considered as an ability of the class.  They are a prestigious item, and should have abilities worthy of their position as "epic."</P><P>I would never call the mage class balanced because they have the epic pet.  If I wanted to compare mages and necros, I would compare two average-geared level 60s without their epics, and I know the result will be that necros are better than mages hands down - I *do* know that the mage class needs help.</P><P>But that doesn't mean that the necro epic should be affected.  The epic should NOT be considered part of the balancing put into a class, because guess what - not everyone's going to get one, not even eventually.  The idea that necros want their epics to be similar to mages is only an expression of the idea that necros and mages should be THE two top pet classes(now add a third beastmaster), with necro pets overall weaker than a mage's.  </P><P>So I don't see where your complaints about necros wanting a pet-based epic is coming from.  Necros have always stood alongside mages as being a pet class, so doesn't it make sense that we get an epic pet?</P><P>Personally, I don't care either way if the necro epic is a DoT or a pet, but I do know *why* people want it to be a pet.</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
